<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Tilbake</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-27 14:06:41</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Well, I completed the Burning Rapier quest nearly singlehandedly at level 35. I post here only to offer a few tips. When I began the game, all the gear I have now seemed a dream so I didnt even bother preplanning. Preplan guys, everything in this game is achievable, just start early to save time. I actually began the quest at level 30 cause I was sick of slow xp. I went across the continent getting drink I could have gotten at earlier levels when I hunted in the spots the drinks were sold. All the info on this page is pretty good; find the drinks you need and where they are sold and pick them up casually as you play the game. When you are ready to do the quest you already have the easy stuff done. Ok, MM is easy...you can sneak all the way to the garden room and if its camped loot the Blood Spirits no problem then sneak out. For OOT its pretty safe. I suggest running to the bank and getting a 49+ NEC to cast Dead Man Floating on you. This will allow you to leveitate and Breath underwater, a SoW is also nice. Now run and catch the boat to OOT, the DMF spell last a long time so worry not. Run to the given /loc and loot the bottle. Having the high level Necro in zone prevented me from buying a Rebreather or Fishbone Earring. To me the hardest part was SolA, but prolly cause im on at odd hours and its not camped much. This is the only time I had real help. I had a guildmate kill Noressa Sparkle and then she even ran and killed the CX Gnome(Thanks Muriel). You dont have to do this in any particular order. The other parts are too easy, the locked door in FP requires a skill of 120 atleast, any high rogue should help you if you arent sufficient skill(Raising Pick Locks is a Bitch, but I open my own doors). The quest isnt as hard as it seems...hell, my friend said he would never do it but once I got mine he changed his mind. Good luck to all you questers...sometimes its not about what a weapon or item does...its more a status symbol. When people see me, they know I earned atleast one item on my inventory =).<BR>
<BR>
  Tilbake Stikke<BR>
  38 BAR/ROG<BR>
  Nightbalde<BR>
  Cazic-Thule</font></td></tr></table>
