<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Vantose</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-01 04:13:17</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
                     Temple of Solusek Ro [ top ]<BR>
                     Printable Info Sheet<BR>
                     Continent: Antonica<BR>
                     Landscape: Town<BR>
                     Level Range: 1 - 50<BR>
                                              Adjacent Zones (1)<BR>
                                              ¤ Lavastorm Mountains<BR>
                                                                       Download Map - size - quality <BR>
                                                                       ¤ soltemple1.jpg - 107 KB - 8/10 <BR>
<BR>
                                        add<BR>
                                                                     <BR>
                                                                                             <BR>
<BR>
                     Burning Rapier<BR>
                     MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP <BR>
                     Skill: Piercing  Atk Delay: 20<BR>
                     DMG: 7<BR>
                     +5 DEX, +5 AGI<BR>
                     Effect: Ignite<BR>
                     WT: 3.5<BR>
                     Class: ROG<BR>
                     Race: ALL<BR>
                                                 Item Icon<BR>
<BR>
                                                           Obtained From<BR>
                                                           Quest<BR>
                                                           Level 30<BR>
                                                                              Additional Info<BR>
                                                                              Type: Weapon, Piercing<BR>
                                                                              Damage Per Second: 7.5<BR>
                                                                              Zone(s): soltemple<BR>
                                                                              Last Updated: 08/18/00<BR>
                                                                              Printable Version<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Description<BR>
Talk to Lon the Redeemed who is in the Temple of Solusek Ro. He will ask you to collect two gems and return them to Ortallius in<BR>
South Ro. <BR>
<BR>
To get the Gem of Stamina you need to talk to Ortallius and he will hand you a note which he wants you to give to Conium<BR>
Darkblade in Dagnor’s Cauldrun. Hand him the note and he will reward you with an axe, called Never Stop Chopping. Now head to<BR>
the bar called Top of the world in Highpass. In the back room is a person named Falyn Farreach. Talk to him and say "never stop<BR>
chopping". He will fill you in on the background of the story, which is quite interesting. Now we head to another bar, by the name of<BR>
The Lumberjack. Talk to Bryan who is on the balcony. Keep a spot open in your main inventory and then give him the axe, in return<BR>
you will receive a container which he wants you to fill with the following ten drinks. <BR>
<BR>
Underfoot Triple Boch -- bought in Kaladim from Tumpy Irontoe <BR>
Tunare's Finest -- bought in Felwithe from Wela Muselender <BR>
Vasty Deep Ale -- bought at the Sister Island in Ocean of Tears <BR>
Lendel's Grand Lauger -- bought in Rivervale from Mac Deeppockets <BR>
Gator Gulp Ale -- bought in the East Commons Tunnel from Bubar <BR>
Frozen Toe Rum -- bought in Halas from Scon McDaniel <BR>
Oblong Bottle (No Drop) -- Found at [-1611 and 2924] in the Ocean of Tears. <BR>
Blood Spirits (No Drop) -- Dropped by a Hemo Enologist in Mistmoore <BR>
Clockwork Oil Stout -- Dropped by a Clockwork CX from Solusek's Eye <BR>
Blackburrow Swig -- You must make this brew yourself. Obtain a Blackburrow Cash and combine the following items in it. 4<BR>
Blackburrow Skins + 2 Blackburrow Scalps + 2 Casks of Ol’ Tujim' Fierce Brew. You do not need a high brewing skill for<BR>
this to succeed. <BR>
<BR>
Combine all these drinks in the box and it will turn into a Box of Spirits. Give the box of spirits to Bryan McGee and you will receive a<BR>
Gem of Stamina. <BR>
<BR>
To get the Gem of Rightousness you need to talk to Noresa Sparkle in West Commons. She asks you to save her from Kizdean Gix.<BR>
She also mentions a Gem Case, which needs two keys to open, and that all three items should be returned to their original crafter to<BR>
find what is inside. Kizdean Gix roams around near Befallen zone in West Commonlands. Kill him and you will receive a note written in<BR>
Goblin, telling you about a Dark Elf outcast who stole a sparkling purse. Head to Solusek's Eye and kill Lynada the Exiled who's in the<BR>
High Shaman room, you will receive the Sparkle Purse. Return the purse to Noresa Sparkle and she gives you one of the keys<BR>
needed to open the Gem Case. The Gem Case is hidden behind a locked door in the slums of East Freeport. The door is locked and<BR>
you must pick it, you need a skill of around 120 to open it. It is also guarded by a dog named Scrapps. No head to the Freeport<BR>
Sewers and find Toxdil. Talk to him about the gem case and gems. He tells you that he has the last key, but will only give it to you for<BR>
the Sparkling Sapphire, which used to be in the Gem Case, but now is in the hands of Noresa. Buy it off Noresa for about 500pp.<BR>
Return this Sapphire to Toxdil, and he gives you the last key necessary to open the Gem Case. Hand the Case and both keys to<BR>
Bubar in the East Commons Tunnel to receive the Gem of Righteousness. <BR>
<BR>
Head back to South Ro and hand both gems to Ortalious, he will reward you with the Burning Rapier. <BR>
<BR>
Note: Since the last update patch, this item not has the Effect of Ignite and no longer acts as a light source.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Vantose <BR>
  Vezeren<BR>
37th rogue from E'ci</font></td></tr></table>
